                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13644837" author="sershe" created="Mon, 29 Apr 2013 20:37:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Idea - add a type flag to the record (optional). If not set, the record is followed by cells as usual. If set, based on enum value the record is followed by custom protobuf record.&lt;br/&gt;
Problem: if protobuf has no generic &quot;skipDelimited&quot; facility or we are unwilling to fake one based on internal format (that starts with size), WAL becomes non-forward-compatible. Can be solved by storing size of custom record for custom records only. That way old versions can skip unrecognized custom WAL entries based on size.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13644899" author="enis" created="Mon, 29 Apr 2013 21:33:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;One option, we discussed at &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2231&quot; title=&quot;Compaction events should be written to HLog&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-2231&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-2231&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; was to add a KeyValue.Type specific for this. But this is fundamentally different than adding the type to the wal edit and not clear whether it will be better. Adding a type to waledit seems more appealing. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
